        public Table(java.lang.String definition,
     java.lang.String... indexes)
      throws se.miun.itm.input.model.InPUTException
        Constructs an empty Table with the specified definition and indexes.
        Parameters:
        definition - The definition of this table.
        indexes - The definitions of the indexes of this table.
        Throws:
        se.miun.itm.input.model.InPUTException - If:
      • The table definition cannot be parsed because of syntax errors.
      • Any of the index definitions cannot be parsed because of syntax errors.
      • Any of the index definitions doesn't conform to the table definition.

      • Table

        public Table(java.lang.String definition,
     java.lang.String[] indexes,
     Table.Row... rows)
      throws se.miun.itm.input.model.InPUTException
        Constructs a Table with the specified definition, indexes and rows.
        Parameters:
        definition - The definition of this table.
        indexes - An array of the definitions of this table's indexes, or null if this table shall not have any indexes.
        rows - The rows that shall be placed in this table.
        Throws:
        se.miun.itm.input.model.InPUTException - If:
      • The table definition cannot be parsed because of syntax errors.
      • Any of the index definitions cannot be parsed because of syntax errors.
      • Any of the index definitions doesn't conform to the table definition.
      • Any of the rows doesn't conform to the table definition.
      • The number of entries in any row isn't equal to the number of columns in this table.
